wikipedia_page.main: Ann Elaine Johnson (born 28 September 1933) is a British sprinter. She competed in the women's 200 metres at the 1952 Summer Olympics. She also represented England in the 220 yards and long jump at the 1954 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Vancouver, Canada.
